<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--RacialAttack     03-10 0138</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Racial Attack,0142</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Brothers Plead Guilty in Attack on Son of Dick Gregory</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BROCKTON, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two brothers pleaded guilty to attacking
the son of comedian-activist Dick Gregory and three other black
youths in an assault the judge called a sign of ``a cancer that is
growing in our society.''
   Kevin Ferreira, 23, and his brother Vernon, 19, pleaded guilty
Tuesday to assault and violating the civil rights of Christian
Gregory and the other blacks.
   Charges are pending against two other white men in the November
1986 attack at a party in Plymouth after a high school football
game.
   Kevin Ferreira said the fight occurred because he was told that
Gregory and his friends referred to the other youths as ``white
honky trash.''
   Brockton Superior Court Judge George N. Hurd Jr. set sentencing
for April 15.
</TEXT>
