<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Cave-in     03-10 0350</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Cave-in,0365</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two Teen-agers Killed in Cave In</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gully caved in on three teen-agers as
they were playing in it, killing two, police said. The third was
able to dig his way out from the 5 feet of dirt and summon help.
   A witness said the cave-in occurred moments after he warned the
boys not to play in the gully.
   Joel Rogers and Damon Deakin, both 13 and from Albuquerque, were
killed in Wednesday's accident, said police spokesman Tony Herrera.
   Herrera said police received a call about 6 p.m. from residents
of a north side trailer park who saw the boys digging in the gully,
then saw a cloud of dust.
   A 14-year-old boy who also fell in managed to dig himself out
and go for help, said Herrera, who would not release the boy's name.
   Neighbors had pulled Rogers out and were trying to revive him
when officers arrived, Herrera said. Paramedics then pulled the
other boy out.
   Deakin was pronounced dead at the scene and Rogers at the
University of New Mexico Hospital.
   Police said the boys were trapped about 20 minutes. A witness
estimated they were under about 5 feet of dirt.
   Dave Wild, a resident of the trailer park, said he warned the
boys it was dangerous to dig in the arroyo.
   He said the boys continued to play in it and moments later he
saw the dust cloud.
   ``I didn't think anything of it,'' he said. ``Then I remembered
the kids digging. I ran out and one of them was yelling that the
other two were trapped inside. I jumped into the arroyo and started
digging.
   ``I kept digging until I got to a foot, then I reached his
head,'' he said. ``I pulled him out and he wasn't breathing.''
   Trailer park manager Kaylin Morris said she heard the boys
talking earlier in the day about digging a tunnel.
   She described them as good kids who often volunteered to do odd
jobs around the trailer park.
   ``The three were inseparable,'' she said. ``It was just like the
Three Musketeers.''
</TEXT>
