<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF-Brazil-Ghanians     03-10 0144</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF-Brazil-Ghanians,0150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ghanians Occupy Airline Office</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Forty-four Ghanian immigrants
occupied a Varig airlines's main office and demanded to be taken to
Canada, upsetting furniture and scuffling with reporters before
leaving, the airline said.
   The 42 adults and two children arrived Feb. 3 in Rio for a
stopover en route from Lagos, Nigeria, to Canada.
   Federal police discovered their passports from Trinidad-Tobago
were false, and the Canadian government refused to let them enter
the country, Varig said in a statement.
   The group was staying in a hotel but the airline recently
stopped paying the bill for meals and accomodations.
   Varig said it would take the group back to Ghana, in West
Africa, if they obtained the necessary travel papers from the
Ghanian Embassy in Brasilia.
   State police surrounded the airline's office but the group left
after several hours.
</TEXT>
