<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BlackhawkCrash-List     03-10 0225</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Blackhawk Crash-List,0234</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>With PM-Copters Collide, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of some of the crashes of the UH-60 Blackhawk
helicopter, the model involved in a collision Tuesday at Fort
Campbell, Ky., that killed 17 soldiers.
   Crashes of the Blackhawk, used by the Army, Air Force and Marine
Corps, have killed about 40 people since 1978, but the
manufacturer, Sikorsky Aircraft, says the craft is about four times
safer than the one it replaced.
   Sept. 16 _ One killed when Army helicopter strikes power line
during NATO exercises at Hanover, West Germany.
   Aug. 14 _ Four killed when Air Force helicopter crashes at Fort
Bragg, N.C.
   March 11, 1986 _ Three killed during Army training flight at
Fort Rucker, Ala.
   Dec. 9, 1985 _ One killed when Army helicopter strikes power
line and crashes 68 miles south of Seoul, South Korea.
   April 18, 1985 _ Three killed in crash on Army training flight
at Fort Rucker.
   March 13, 1985 _ Eight killed in Army training flight at Fort
Bragg.
   Feb. 2, 1984 _ Four killed when Army helicopter crashes during
war games in Honduras.
   Oct. 18, 1983 _ Four killed in crash during Army night training
mission near Mount Ranier in Washington.
   Oct. 4, 1983 _ Two killed when Army helicopter crashes in
Caribbean Sea near entrance to Panama Canal.
</TEXT>
