<HEAD>Bomb Story Wins Man 15-Minute Prison Term</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAPE TOWN, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gardener was sentenced to 15
minutes in prison for telling a police officer there was a bomb in
the president's office.
   The mixed-race gardener, Basil Von Dieman, told a magistrate's
court on Wednesday that he was only joking when he made the comment
to a policeman Jan. 28 while working outside President P.W. Botha's
office in Cape Town.
   Magistrate P.M. Louw sentenced Von Dieman, 42, to three years in
prison, but suspended the sentence except for the 15-minute period
prior to the court's recess for morning tea.
</TEXT>
