<HEAD>Warsaw Pact Minister To Meet This Month</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PRAGUE, Czechoslovakia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The foreign ministers of the seven
Warsaw Pact member countries will meet in Sofia, Bulgaria, at the
end of March, the Czechoslovak state news agency CTK reported.
   The report Wednesday did not disclose other details, but an
official at the Foreign Ministry said the Sofia meeting, believed
to be a regular session, was agreed to when the Soviet bloc foreign
ministers met in Prague last month.
   In their meeting on Feb. 23, the foreign ministers approved the
Soviet Union's stand in the latest talks in Moscow between Soviet
Foreign Minister Eduard Shevardnadze and U.S. Secretary of State
George P. Shultz.
   Shevardnadze briefed the participants at that meeting on his
talks with Shultz on Feb. 21-22.
