<DATELINE>SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Assembly Speaker Willie Brown says
Jesse Jackson could win the California primary, which could decide
the Democratic presidential nomination.
   Brown, Jackson's national campaign chairman, also said his
candidate could have won two or three more states on Super Tuesday
if he had had money for television advertisements.
   ``We may well determine the Democratic nomination with the
California vote,'' Brown told reporters Wednesday.
   ``Probably Jackson is the favorite at the moment'' in the June 7
California primary, one of the last in the country, Brown said.
   Brown, D-San Francisco, said Jackson will be in California on
March 19 and 20, including a visit to the state Democratic
convention in Palm Springs that weekend.
   Brown, who said he will be putting together a series of
nationwide concerts, featuring stars who support Jackson, to raise
money for the campaign, added that Jackson will be in California
``four or five times in April and on a regular basis in the month
of May.
