<HEAD>New Correspondent for New Haven</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Larry Rosenthal, a newsman in the
Baltimore bureau of The Associated Press since 1981, has been named
correspondent in New Haven.
   Hartford Chief of Bureau Mary Anne Rhyne announced the
appointment Wednesday.
   Rosenthal, 33, was a reporter for the Central Maine Morning
Sentinel in his hometown of Waterville, Maine, before joining the
AP. He is a graduate of Hobart College.
   In New Haven, Rosenthal succeeds Susan Okula, who has taken
maternity leave and will return to the AP's Hartford bureau.
