<TEXT>
   The Writers Guild of America took a break
from its 5-day-old strike against movie and television producers to
honor a married, scriptwriting couple with its annual Screen Laurel
Award.
   Irving Ravetch and Harriet Frank most recently wrote ``Stanley
and Iris,'' for a production to begin this summer starring Robert
DeNiro and Jane Fonda in the title roles.
   Their film credits also include ``Norma Rae,'' ``Murphy's
Romance'' and ``Hud,'' for which they received the New York Film
