   Emperor Hirohito and Empress Nagako left Thursday
for a one-week rest at their seaside villa, their first trip
outside the palace since the emperor underwent abdominal surgery
last September.
   The emperor, 86, has recovered well enough to travel by train to
the villa on the Izu Peninsula, southwest of Tokyo, an Imperial
