<1ST_LINE>r a AM-TeenCop     03-10 0311</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Teen Cop,0318</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Youth Arrested After Prostitution `Bust'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUSTIN, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police arrested a 17-year-old who allegedly
donned a sheriff-style uniform and posed as a lawman in order to
have sex with a professional escort.
   The youth was arrested on charges of impersonating a public
officer and released on $3,000 bond, authorities said Thursday.
   Austin vice investigator Earl Hall said the youth entered a
motel Feb. 24 wearing a brown uniform, a heavy police-type jacket
and a gun belt with .38-caliber snub-nose pistol.
   The youth identified himself as a member of the Sheriff's
Department of Williamson County, working on a prostitution case,
Hall said. The man called an Austin escort service and then asked
for a room in which to make an arrest, he said.
   When the escort arrived at the room, the youth told her she was
under arrest for prostitution but implied he would let her go if
she had sex with him, Hall said. They left the motel after the
manager came to the room and asked the youth to pay for it, he said.
   The youth was then refused rooms at two other motels, Hall said.
   At a fourth motel, the youth said he was an Austin police
officer, paid for a room and had sexual intercourse with the
escort, Hall said. He then released her, saying no charges would be
filed, he said.
   The woman then got her boyfriend, who confronted the
impersonator at a gas station and took his gun belt and briefcase
in an effort to learn his identity, Hall said.
   The youth reported a robbery to police. They arrested the woman
and her boyfriend that day but released them.
   The youth was arrested the same day when he allegedly tried to
reclaim his property at the police station. He was released pending
further investigation, then rearrested Wednesday on the
impersonation charge.
</TEXT>
