<2ND_LINE>AM-Pirelli-Firestone,0216</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Pirelli Sets Borrowing Facility for Firestone Takeover</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A unit of Pirelli SpA arranged a $2.3 billion
credit line Thursday through SBCI Swiss Bank Corp. to finance its
takeover bid for Firestone Tire and Rubber Co., SBCI said.
   Veere Inc., a unit of Pirelli and Pirelli Societe Internationale
SA, will use $1.93 billion dollars to finance the $58
dollar-a-share bid for the U.S. tire maker, the bank said.
   The bid by the Milan-based tire maker was announced Monday after
being rumored for more than a week.
   The remainder of the credit line will go to refinance ``certain
obligations of Firestone,'' the bank said. It did not elaborate.
   The bank also did not state the terms of the credit facility,
which is being fully underwritten by Swiss Bank Corp. and Credit
Suisse.
   Pirelli has said it will spin off part of Firestone to France's
Michelin & Co. But Pirelli's offer was made after Firestone already
had agreed to sell its tire business to Japan's Bridgestone Corp.
for about $1.25 billion by setting up a joint venture that would
give the Japanese company a 75 percent stake in Firestone's
factories and retail network.
   Analysts have said they expect Bridgestone to make a counter
offer.
